lead_paragraph: President Benigno S. Aquino III has overseen nearly six years of strong growth, but many voters say his administration has been indecisive and ineffective.

headline.print_headline: Candidates to Lead the Philippines Tap Into Dissatisfaction With the Government
headline.main: Rodrigo Duterte and Other Candidates Seeking to Lead Philippines Tap Into Aquino Fatigue

snippet: President Benigno S. Aquino III has overseen nearly six years of strong growth, but many voters say his administration has been indecisive and ineffective.
abstract: Dissatisfaction among voters in Philippines with perceived government indecision and inefficacy has buoyed outsider candidates like Rodrigo Duterte, Grace Poe and Ferdinand R Marcos Jr, despite successes of outgoing Pres Benigno Aquino; critics say growth under Aquino has not been felt by ordinary citizens.
